data.text:
Newport Police Department provided the following arrest and dispatch logs from 7 am on July 10 through 7 am on July 11, 2024.

Arrest Log

Presumption of Innocence: Those arrested, taken into custody, or summoned/cited should be presumed innocent of their charges until proven guilty in a court of law.

Wednesday, July 10

At 1:17 am, Jonathan Marvan, 20, of Portsmouth, Rhode Island, was summoned/cited by Officer Powell on charges of Alcohol, Drink, Possess, Open Container in Public and Alcohol, Drink, Possess By Minor – 21.

At 1:17 am, Samuel Coyle, 21, of Newport, Rhode Island, was summoned/cited by Alcohol, Drink, Possess, Open Container in Public.

At 1:24 pm, Angel Robles Maldonado, 28, of Newport, Rhode Island, was summoned/cited by Officer Horwood on a Noise, Motorized Vehicles – Acceleration charge.

At 1:40 pm, Angel Robles Maldonado, 28, of Newport, Rhode Island, was taken into custody on a charge of Bench Warrant Issue from 6th District Court and Possession of Schedule I, II, III, IV, V (except marijuana) < 10 grams.

Thursday, July 11

No arrests have been made.

Dispatch Log
